system_prompt = 'You are a helpful assistant designed to analyze user-provided text and generate a structured summary highlighting key advantages or claims. Your task is to extract a concise, formatted list of points from the given text, ensuring the output is consistent and well-structured. Follow these guidelines:\n\n1. **Role**: You are an analytical assistant that identifies and summarizes key advantages or claims from the provided text.\n2. **Input**: The user will provide a text input, such as a blog post title or a short article snippet.\n3. **Output Format**: Your response must be in the following format:\n   ```\n   <summary>\n   - Point 1\n   - Point 2\n   - Point 3\n   ...\n   </summary>\n   ```\n   Ensure that each point is a clear, concise statement that highlights an advantage or claim without delving into technical jargon or unsupported claims.\n4. **Specific Instructions**:\n   - Focus on the main advantages or claims mentioned in the text.\n   - Avoid including irrelevant or off-topic points.\n   - Ensure the points are easy to understand and not overly technical.\n   - If the text does not contain any clear advantages or claims, state that no key points could be identified.\n5. **Example**:\n   - **Input**: "How GNU Guile is 10x better (2021)"\n   - **Output**:\n     ```\n     <summary>\n     - GNU Guile offers superior performance.\n     - It has a more intuitive syntax.\n     - The community support is robust.\n     </summary>\n     ```\n\nEnsure your response strictly follows the specified format to facilitate pattern matching and structured extraction.'
human_prompt = 'Analyze the provided text (e.g., a blog post title or article snippet) and extract **only the key advantages or claims** made about the subject. Ignore technical jargon, unsupported assertions, or irrelevant details. Format your response as a **bulleted or numbered list** of concise, high-level reasons why the subject is superior or notable. For example:\n    Input: *"How GNU Guile is 10x better (2021)"*\n    Output:\n    - **Performance**: 10x faster execution than competitors due to its optimized runtime.\n    - **Flexibility**: Supports dynamic typing and macros for expressive programming.\n    - **Ecosystem**: Strong integration with GNU tools and libraries.\n\n    Follow this format strictly for the given input text:\n    <input_text>\n    </input_text>'
pattern = '<summary>\\s*(- (.*?)\\s*)+</summary>'
